&lt;p style="margin-bottom: 15px; font-style: italic;"&gt;According to multiple reports, the Defense Department barred press photographers from subsequent briefings after aides to Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth objected to images from a recent press conference they considered “unflattering.” Yes, in the middle of a war, the Pentagon is apparently conducting a counteroffensive against mean photographers. The solution? Ban photographers.&lt;/p&gt;
